Here's a quick update. I rarely make updates lately because I'm not very happy about my returns. I'm more motivated to make updates when we do great. Portfolio is up +0.4% vs. SPY +2.1% MTD.

It's not easy beating the market when you're playing very defensive. It's the choice I made to protect my portfolio and I'm sticking with it. I don't care if it doesn't pay off right away, I'm a patient investor. At least we're still making small gains and protecting our portfolio while we wait for better entries/opportunities. My other portfolio which is mostly long equity (especially in GAMMA (GOOG, $AAPL, MSFT, META, $AMZN) & semiconductors ($NVDA, $TSM, $AMD, ASML, etc.) was on fire today. I don't chase, I simply wait to allocate more when opportunities come to us. Until then we'll have to settle with our smaller gains. Cheers 🍻
